BEAT egg product and milk in medium bowl with wire whisk until well blended. Add patty pieces and onion; mix well. Pour into nonstick or lightly oiled skillet. COOK on medium heat until set, stirring frequently. Sprinkle with cheese; cover. Cook until cheese is melted. SPOON a scant 1/2 cup egg product mixture onto each tortilla; fold in ends and roll up burrito style. Serve with salsa, if desired.